            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 2061: <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Documents</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the <gloss type="from">Soviet Delegation</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Council of Foreign Ministers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 63</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-09">9 May,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Future Procedure of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">amendment by the soviet delegation to the proposal of the
                        u.s. delegation (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">c.f.m. (46)</gloss> 62)</hi>
                    <note n="94" xml:id="d120fn94">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_310">p. 310</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Para, b) to read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>1) To call, in accordance with the agreement reached at Moscow, a
                                Peace Conference to meet in Paris on 15th June, <hi rend="italic">on
                                    the understanding that agreement will be reached on the proposed
                                    Peace Treaties</hi>, to which draft treaties shall be submitted
                                so that in the final drafting of the treaties the Council shall have
                                the benefit and assistance of the recommendations made by the Peace
                                Conference.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Add the following paragraph to the U.S. draft: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>c) To instruct the Deputies of the Foreign Ministers to submit not
                                later than 5th June for the approval of the Council of Foreign
                                Ministers, drafts of the proposed Peace Treaties with Italy,
                                Roumania, Bulgaria, Hungary and Finland, in order that these drafts
                                may be presented to a Peace Conference on behalf of the Council of
                                Foreign Ministers. The Council of Foreign Ministers to approve at
                                the <pb facs="0342" n="322" xml:id="pg_322"/> same time draft rules
                                of procedure for the Peace Conference and the invitations to the
                                Governments who are to attend it.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>, 10 May, 1946.<note n="95" xml:id="d120fn95">This proposal was originally circulated to the Council of Foreign Ministers
                        during its 14th Meeting, May 9, 6 p.m.; see the United States Delegation
                        Record of that meeting, <ref target="#pg_311">p. 311</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
